Libya Looting Cost Turkish Builders $100 Million, Hurriyet Says

-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 
2011-02-27T12:55:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-27/libya-looting-cost-turkish-builders-100-million-hurriyet-says.html
Turkish contractors lost about $100
million as a result of looting in  Libya  following the unrest in
the North African country, Hurriyet reported, citing unnamed
officials from companies operating there.  Machinery, office buildings and construction sites were
affected by looting, the Istanbul-based newspaper said. Turkish
contractors have a project backlog of $15.3 billion in Libya,
Foreign Trade Minister Zafer Caglayan said on Feb. 21.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net . 